overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application. The agent performed an initial assessment, identifying several
  critical and medium-priority gaps in the existing implementation compared to
  the provided specification. These gaps included missing severity scales,
  specific disorder detections (COMISA, Insufficient Sleep Syndrome), lack of
  outbound resources, unweighted scoring for EDS, and incomplete data export.
  The agent then systematically addressed each identified gap, updating the
  application's data models, validation logic, user interface components, and
  report generation (both on-screen and PDF) to incorporate the new features.
  This iterative process ensured the questionnaire became more robust,
  clinically relevant, and aligned with the user's detailed requirements,
  providing a more comprehensive assessment and reporting system.
